# Keep Docker build contexts small (the production Dockerfile and
# `.clusterfuzzlite/Dockerfile` both `COPY .`): exclude VCS data, build
# outputs, the fuzz working dirs, and everything not needed to compile
# the workspace — so a docs/CI/chart change doesn't invalidate the image
# build context. The committed sources (crates/, fuzz/fuzz_targets,
# fuzz/seeds) and the manifests (Cargo.toml/Cargo.lock) are kept.
.git/
.github/
target/
fuzz/target/
fuzz/corpus/
fuzz/artifacts/
fuzz/coverage/
book/
scratch/
docs/
deploy/
*.md
LICENSE
# NB: do NOT exclude .clusterfuzzlite/ — its Dockerfile `COPY`s
# .clusterfuzzlite/build.sh from the build context.
